                  <!--saint-->
                 
               <floruit notBefore="0500" notAfter="0600">He was one of the most important saints 
                  of the Aksumite period and renowned as one
                  of the early founders of monasticism and asceticism in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName>. He came from 
                  <placeName ref="wd:Q406">Constantinople</placeName> during the reign of King <persName ref="PRS3732ellaGab">ʾƎlla Gabaz</persName>. 
                  He was chiefly active in <placeName ref="LOC5575Saraye">Sarāye</placeName> and <placeName ref="LOC1298Akkala">ʾAkkala Guzāy</placeName>.
                  He was said to be the founder of the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2296DabraL">Dabra Libānos</placeName>.
                 
                     
